        public double[] Dijkstra(GraphByMatrix<T,E> g,
                         Vertex<T> v)
        This method realize the algorithm Dijkstra. This method computes the minimum path cost of one vertex with all vertices of the graph.
        Parameters:
        g - The graph.
        v - The vertex where the method will compute all the minimum path costs of this vertex to the all vertices of the graph.
        Returns:
        An array of distances where each position is the minimum path cost of the vertex v with the vertex in the position of the distances array.(The position that has the value 0.0 is the position of the vertex v which the method compute all the minimum path costs.
